content: I love it!!

This is SO easy and SO useful and you're never going to spend under $4 for such return on investment again! In Windows-land I use Presonus Studio One and Reaper, and am used to complicated settings and the beauty of J4T is how simple and foolproof it is. I wonder out loud to suggest to developer to have the latency check as the first thing that shows up on a new device, because it's incredibly sad to see the recent review where its called junk, yet it's SO easy to set the latency properly. I've had a blast recording acoustic guitar with headphones into my Android phone. The quality has been better than I expected once I bring the files into my computer's DAW. I also beta test for one of the best audio noise reduction suites and thought this would be a lot noisier than it is. But with a headphones, closed ear buds the other tracks won't bleed into the main one. If I find faults they're noting really. The left arrow to get to the settings screen is always close to the fader and screws it up, but that's minor. And like others here I wonder what the metronome could do as well. I love the idea of recording the metronome to one track, because that would make it a LOT easier to sync this once you brought it back to a major DAW to work around. My favorite Android is a $9.99 Best Buy Huawei with no SIM in my area and the microphone CAN sound pretty good! Experiment! In conclusion, this is the best at what it does, and I feel so strongly that this is my first review ever for anything Google :-) I emailed the guy and he's real cool too. Cheers bro!

... and I love it!   Just a few thoughts/suggestions:  I found it difficult at first, but now it's fluid. (Just keep at it if you're finding it hard to use -- it seems to do mostly everything you would need it to do, assuming it works well on your device) I cannot use many effects. They seem to take too much device memory. But it doesn't bother me since the original track can be relatively good quality.      One suggestion to JT4 users:  if you create lots of files, export them to MP3 as you make them!   (not once a year like I am currently trying to do... a major time-sucker!)    Would love to see a batch converter built in, but it's really an amazing app that I am very grateful for.

I got this a few devices ago and at the time it was good. My other devices I had to adjust latency so the tracks lined up. For those who are complaining about that, read the directions you can set a custom latency offset to fix the problem. Those that are complaining about quality, do some reading on real recording and the costs of profesional mikes. Anyway i just upgraded to a galaxy note 10.1 2014 model and it works so much better on this tablet. No need to adjust for hardware latency. I use an adapter that I got off amazon to plug in a real mike and headset. The recording is simple the quality is as good as I get from a typical pc. (Remember quality is hardware dependent, that includes the mic and the phone/tablet. Not to even get into environmental setup issues with recording). Anyway normally I don't take the time to post reviews like this but I saw all the negative ones and knew I needed to clear up a few.  Keep up the good work on this app!

That being said, there is 1 issue on my device... -------- Model: Samsung Galaxy Precedent [SCH-M828C] -------- OS Ver: Android 2.2.2 [Froyo] *Rooted* -------- Issue: When headphones are plugged in, recording is not possible. Playback with, or without, headphones is perfect. I can listen to tracks just fine. However, if the headphones are plugged in the app records a track (filling up the track bar) with no sound in it. A "blank" track. It behaves and looks normal, but when that track is played back there is only silence. It's as if plugging the headphones in disables the phone-mic because it's expecting a hands-free-mic. ***THIS MAY NOT BE THE APPS FAULT, so I still give it 5 stars...I just wanted to write this review in case anyone else with this phone model decides to download this app, you are warned. Still, I can't say this enough, this is an awesome app!
